KW  - Efficiency
KW  - Equity
KW  - Incentive-compatible contracts
AB  - While the efficiency of certain contractual choices has been well established, less attention has been given to the distributional outcomes of contracting in natural resource-based industries. Data from a case study of seed gatherers in Honduras demonstrates that workers paid under a relative payment system receive an earnings premium of about 25%, of which 40% cannot be explained by observed differences in worker productivity. A theoretical agency model is outlined in the appendix to explain why workers under tournaments necessarily enjoy a higher return than those under piece-rates, implying a more skewed income distribution as suggested in the efficiency wage literature.
ER  - 

